Let \(K_{S,\X,\alpha}   \{\X: \exists f:\Gn\to \X^n \text{ which \(\alpha\)-preserves \(S\)}\}\).
   For (i), note that if \(f\) \(\alpha\)-preserves \(S\), then it necessarily \(\beta\)-preserves \(S\). So the set of \(\beta\)-preserving embeddings is larger, therefore an infimum over this larger set is only smaller.

   For (ii), note if \(f\) \(\alpha\)-preserves \(S\), then it necessarily \(\alpha\)-preserves \(T\).   So the set of embeddings which \(\alpha\)-preserves \(T\) is only larger, therefore an infimum over this larger set is only smaller.

